========================================================================
ARCHITECTURE REFERENCE
========================================================================

Key gotchas for future developers:

1. PIO decomposition type MUST match Fortran array type. PIO_REAL needs
   real(4). Mismatch garbles output with NO runtime error.

2. Fortran sequence association: array(pcols,nlev) passed to dummy(ncol,
   nlev) with ncol<pcols reads wrong memory at k>1. Pass (1:ncol,:).

3. apply_masked packs mask as level numlev+1. One alltoallv + one SpMV.
   No frac_b needed — valid_frac IS the correct denominator.

4. MPAS framework calls AM init twice. register_var guards duplicates.

5. Fill flow: AM → 1e34 at source → caller zeros + mask=0 → apply_masked
   → SHR_FILL_VALUE (1e20) at output → _FillValue attribute matches.

6. Map file has n_a = N_total (global cell IDs). Identity mapping used.

7. MPAS remapped output bypasses stream manager (direct PIO).
   File rotation via check_rotate + register_var replay.
